Wrapping Up Cypress

06

Cypress is a fantastic testing tool that brings stability I appreciate. Because Cypress doesn’t care what framework your application was written in, if you write good tests it should be an easier transition if you end up doing a rewrite.

There’s a lot to learn in Cypress that we didn’t discuss here. Read through their docs to get an idea for its commands. For example, the go command is helpful for navigating through the browser history.

Check out the Cypress Testing Library add-on that introduces the ability to use the DOM style querying inside of Cypress. This is great for testing using findByRole or findByLabelText.

As you move forward writing tests, think about what your most important user flows are. Prioritize the flows to test by traffic or revenue they’re responsible for.
